next
  Summary: Spawner-record balance, spawn size, squad refill, crowded-area steering, Inventory Balance moved to AlifeGuard

  Respawn Pacing
    - Changed Smart Balance from kill-counting to a per-map balance over the game's own spawner records:
      how many squads each spawner is allowed versus how many are alive right now, per faction, mutants as one group.
      Depleted factions get respawn cooldowns advanced in proportion to how depleted they are, so a wiped faction returns at full speed while a dented one gets a nudge.
      Overgrown factions and spawners in crowded areas get cooldowns delayed, never blocking a spawn, and healthy maps are left completely alone.
    - Territory changes from other mods (conquest, infestation) shift the balance target automatically,
      so a captured smart terrain gets populated by its new owner and drifts back after the effect expires.
    - Added a ceiling on delayed cooldowns: a delay never leaves a smart terrain waiting longer than the configured maximum (default 12 game-hours),
      pairing with the minimum-cooldown floor (default 2 game-hours) so every correction stays inside a configurable window.
    - Accelerations are only spent on spawners the game will actually fire: disabled, unreachable, player-adjacent,
      and level-restricted spawners are skipped, as is everything while a wish for peace holds.
    - Map markers now also mark delayed smart terrains, and the right-click stats show advances and delays.
    - Removed the death counter, kill thresholds, and the vermin filter.

  Spawn Size
    - Added Spawn Size: new squads of a faction that is losing across the whole Zone arrive with more members,
      up to their own configured maximum, in proportion to how badly the faction is losing.
      A faction merely dented on one map spawns normal squads. Strength slider and toggle in MCM, on by default.

  Squad Refill
    - Added Squad Refill: squads that fell below their own minimum size regain one member per pass.
      Nothing in the game repairs a squad once it loses members, and a surviving remnant blocks its respawn slot forever, so maps fill with one-man ghost squads.
      The refill runs only on squads far from the player, skips crowded areas and overgrown factions, and stops at the squad's own configured minimum. Toggle in MCM, on by default.

  General
    - Added a crowded area threshold: areas already holding many off-screen NPCs receive no accelerated respawns and no squad repairs,
      and their spawners are delayed, steering recovery toward the empty parts of a map instead of feeding existing piles.
    - MCM restructured into one page per system: General, Respawn Pacing, Spawn Size, Squad Refill, Development. Reset MCM settings after updating.

  Compatibility
    - Warfare is no longer supported alongside Smart Balance. Its population model fights any external balancing. Disable AlifeBalance when running Warfare.

  Inventory Balance
    - Removed Inventory Balance. The system moved to AlifeGuard, where it is called Inventory Guard, with identical behavior.
      Configure it in AlifeGuard's MCM. Reset MCM settings after updating.
      DLTX overrides of configs/alifebalance/ab_inventory_policy.ltx must repoint to configs/alifeguard/ag_inventory_policy.ltx.

1.1.2
  Summary: Cull caps aligned with the loot policy, respawn pacing reads the active config, platform status

  - Added dynamic checking of xlibs and xray-monolith/AOEngine versions with a compatibility verdict.
  - An outdated xlibs no longer crashes AlifeBalance on load. The dependency check now shows the update-xlibs message instead of a raw script error from the MCM platform footer.
  - Aligned the inventory cull caps with the AlifePlus loot policy. Rifle ammo drops from 120 to 45 and launcher grenades from 6 to 3, so culling and looting agree on how much an NPC keeps.
  - Respawn pacing now reads the respawn cooldown actually in effect, and honors respawns being turned off. It no longer accelerates smarts whose respawns are disabled, and its spawn-rate scaling matches the engine's.

1.1.1
  Summary: Smoke grenade cull, 12h scan cooldown, AOEngine compatibility, fewer engine warnings

  - Added AOEngine v0.55+ support.
  - Changed inventory balance to cull smoke grenades from NPC inventories, including one held in the
    grenade slot. Smoke crashes the game when an NPC throws it on current exes.
  - Changed the inventory scan cooldown to 12 game-hours (was 24), so NPCs are trimmed twice per game-day.
  - Fixed a burst of "trying to use a destroyed object" warnings logged when a creature despawns during a scan.

1.1.0
  Summary: Inventory Balance, equipped ammo coverage, DLTX policy, Smart Balance rename, MCM split

  Inventory Balance
    - Stops NPC hoarding so anti-loot mods are no longer needed.
      Scanner trims online stalkers one per frame, rescans each at most once per game-day.
      Solves what anti-loot mods avoid: jackpot bodies, and saves filling toward the 65k engine cap.
      Scans random long-lived stalkers (gulag survivors, patrols). Companions, story NPCs, traders skipped.
    - Quest items, equipped gear, story_id items, companion gifts, player-strapped weapons never released.
    - Equipped rifle and pistol ammo bounded per tier.

  Policy
    - ab_inventory_policy.ltx (DLTX-overridable) holds per-category ceilings.
      Shares LTX shape with AlifePlus ap_trade_policy.ltx and ap_stash_policy.ltx.

  Smart Balance
    - Smart Pacing renamed to Smart Balance. Label only, no behavior change.
    - Death counter now credits every non-vermin death (was filtered to exclude protected NPCs).

  MCM
    - Split into Smart Balance and Inventory Balance tabs (was a single General tab).
      Existing MCM settings reset to defaults on upgrade.
    - Removed Show Status and Reset Counters buttons from the Development tab.

  Compatibility
    - Disable any NPC anti-loot addon (NPC Stop Looting Dead Bodies, Weapons Drop on Bodies, BoltBeGone).
      Vanilla looting is the source Inventory Balance trims, without it the scanner has nothing to do.

1.0.2
  Summary: Crash fix on xlibs 1.7.0
  Fixed:
    Fixed: Crash in Smart Pacing on xlibs 1.7.0 at ab_recipe.script:141. Adopt renamed xsmart.find_smarts_spawning (was xsmart.find_smarts_with_recipe pre-1.7.0). Requires xlibs 1.7.0+.

1.0.1
  Summary: Crash fix on malformed respawn params, third-party respawn-delay compatibility
  Fixed:
    Fixed: Crash in Smart Pacing budget evaluation when scanning malformed or misconfigured smart terrains whose respawn_params.num condlist has no default branch.
  Compatibility:
    Skip smart terrains whose last_respawn_update is set to a future game-time by another mod. Honors third-party deferred-respawn intent instead of overriding it.

1.0.0
  First release. Advances respawn cooldowns at smart terrains where combat has produced deaths, so active regions recover faster without affecting the rest of the map.
